BRAZEN thieves drove off with a haul of designer trainers after stealing them from a lorry they were stored in. Thieves nab designer trainers after stealing lorry they were stored in BRAZEN thieves drove off with a haul of designer trainers after stealing them from a lorry they were stored in.The trailer was packed full and parked up at M8 Services Harthill, when it was targeted.Thieves broke into the vehicle driving off with the loot.It happened between 6pm on Tuesday and 7am on Wednesday, while the trailer was parked. A Police Scotland spokesman said: &quot;Officers are continuing enquiries and appealing for information after a trailer was broken into whilst parked at a service station.&quot; 